<h2 id="integration-strategy">🔗 Integration Strategy That Actually Works</h2>

Buying great tools matters less than connecting them properly. We have audited operators running best-in-class software with zero integration—manually exporting CSVs from their booking system to import into their CRM weekly. That is not a tech stack; that is expensive chaos.

Your integration priorities:

<strong>Booking → CRM sync must be automatic and bidirectional.</strong> New bookings create or update customer records. Customer notes in your CRM should be visible to staff handling bookings.

<strong>Booking → Communication triggers should be event-based.</strong> Confirmation emails, reminders, and follow-ups fire automatically based on booking status changes.

<strong>All data → Analytics must flow without manual intervention.</strong> If someone has to pull reports from three systems and combine them in a spreadsheet, your stack is failing.

Rezdy offers native integrations with major CRM platforms and a well-documented API for custom connections. Most operators can achieve full integration using Zapier for simpler workflows or direct API integration for complex requirements.

