<h2 id="implementation-timeline">📅 Realistic Implementation Timeline</h2>

We are skeptical of vendors promising "go live in 24 hours." Yes, you can technically process a booking that quickly. Building a properly configured system that actually reduces your workload takes longer.

<strong>Week 1:</strong> Platform setup, product catalog creation, pricing rules configuration. Expect 15-20 hours of focused work from your operations lead.

<strong>Week 2:</strong> Channel integrations, payment processing setup, staff account creation. Test bookings through every channel. Fix the issues you discover.

<strong>Week 3:</strong> Communication workflow configuration, CRM integration, staff training. Run parallel operations with your old system if possible.

<strong>Week 4:</strong> Full cutover, monitoring for edge cases, optimization based on real usage patterns.

Rushing this process creates problems that take months to untangle. We have seen operators spend 6+ months fixing data quality issues caused by sloppy initial setup.

